Going down to the SCIF this week wasn’t a publicity stunt. It wasn’t about defending the President. 

It was about demanding fairness, due process and full transparency to Floridians and the American people. 

Read my latest in the @orlandosentinel: https://www.orlandosentinel.com/opinion/guest-commentary/os-op-michael-waltz-congressman-editorial-response-20191026-ftzbx7y6szg5jbkfm37phevjda-story.html …

It's been three days since @RepAdamSchiff missed the deadline to provide transcripts of witness testimony in the impeachment process. 

This is completely unacceptable. The American people deserve transparency! pic.twitter.com/BYql1AuoaA

This is patently unfair to this institution which I fought and risked my life for. 

I demand better. The American people demand better. And the @orlandosentinel should demand better too.

It should outrage ALL of us, including the media, that we are distracted by impeachment. Meanwhile, we still don’t have legislative action on:

-Fixing the cost of healthcare
-Funding our military (first time with no military budget in 59 years) 
-Fixing our aging infrastructure
This is all while information is selectively leaked from these committees, sometimes actually while the hearings are going on.

Today, proceedings are held in secret and the transcripts of these witness testimonies still aren’t available to members of Congress or to the public, despite being unclassified. 

How can I be expected to vote on impeaching the President of the United States with no information?

In 1974, the House openly debated and passed rules to impeachment proceedings. 

The rules were agreed on. 

Both parties to subpoena witnesses and allowed the executive branch to have counsel present.

We’re not seeing the same in 2019.

Disappointed the @orlandosentinel didn’t once reach out to me about this. 

I would have been more than happy to explain to the Sentinel why I attended this press conference, as I did with other outlets. 

This was not a stunt. It was a push for transparency and fairness. https://twitter.com/orlandosentinel/status/1187628850408284160 …
